Definition: from the same as {{h8602}}; quagmire; Tophel, a place near the Desert; Tophel.
from an unused root meaning to smear; plaster (as gummy) or slime; (figuratively) frivolity; foolish things, unsavoury, untempered.
from {{h644}}; cookery, i.e. (concretely) a cake; baked piece.
a primitive root; to equalize, i.e. straighten (intransitive or transitive); figuratively, to compose; set in order, make straight.
from {{h6452}}; ford; Tiphsach, a place in Mesopotamia; Tipsah.
from {{h6426}}; fearfulness; terrible.
from {{h6419}}; intercession, supplication; by implication, a hymn; prayer.
from the same as {{h8602}}; frivolity; folly, foolishly.
of foreign derivation; Tartan, an Assyrian; Tartan.
of foreign derivation; the title of a Persian deputy or governor; Tirshatha.
a primitive root; to sew; (women that) sew (together).
a primitive root; to drum, i.e. play (as) on the tambourine; taber, play with timbrels.
from {{h8628}}; a blast of a trumpet; sound.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8626}}; to straighten up, i.e. confirm; establish.
from {{h7760}}; a deposit, i.e. pledging; fellowship.
or תְּשֻׁבָה; from {{h7725}}; a recurrence (of time or place); a reply (as returned); answer, be expired, return.
or תְּקֹעִי; patronymically from {{h8620}}; a Tekoite or inhabitant of Tekoah; Tekoite.
a form of {{h8619}}; Tekoa, a place in Palestine; Tekoa, Tekoah.
or תְּשֻׁעָה; from {{h7768}} in the sense of {{h3467}}; rescue (literal or figurative, persons, national or spiritual); deliverance, help, safety, salvation, victory.
from {{h8630}}; powerful; mightier.
multiple from {{h8672}}; ninety; ninety.
of foreign derivation; Teresh, a eunuch of Xerxes; Teresh.
or (masculine) תִּשְׁעָה; perhaps from {{h8159}} through the idea of a turn to the next or full number ten; nine or (ordinal) ninth; nine (  -teen,   -teenth, -th).
or תְּקֻפָה; from {{h5362}}; a revolution, i.e. (of the sun) course, (of time) lapse; circuit, come about, end.
probably for {{h766}}; a pole (as a mast or flagstaff); beacon, mast.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8179}}; a door; by implication, a palace; gate mouth.
(Aramaic) from {{h8651}}; a doorkeeper; porter.
from {{h7477}}; reeling; astonishment, trembling.
patrial from an unused name meaning gate; a Tirathite or inhabitant of an unknown Tirah; Tirathite.
plural from {{h7495}}; a healer; Teraphim (singular or plural) a family idol; idols(-atry), images, teraphim.
from {{h7521}}; delightsomeness; Tirtsah, a place in Palestine; also an Israelitess; Tirzah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8633}}; power; might, strength.
probably of foreign derivation (compare {{h8659}}); a gem, perhaps the topaz; beryl.

probably the same as {{h8658}} (as the region of the stone, or the reverse); Tarshish, a place on the Mediterranean, hence, the ephithet of a merchant vessel (as if for or from that port); also the name of a Persian and of an Israelite; Tarshish, Tharshish.
of foreign derivation; Tattenai, a Persian; Tatnai.
from {{h7722}}; a crashing or loud clamor; crying, noise, shouting, stir.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8254}}; to balance; Tekel, be weighed.
from {{h7235}}; multiplication, i.e. percentage or bonus in addition to principal; increase, unjust gain.
a denominative from {{h7270}}; to cause to walk; teach to go.
probably for {{h8653}}; a reeling; Taralah, a place in Palestine; Taralah.
from {{h7235}}; multiplication, i.e. progeny; increase.
from {{h6965}}; an opponent; rise up against.
from {{h8628}} (in the musical sense); a trumpet; trumpet.
a primitive root; to overpower; prevail (against).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8630}}; to become (causatively, make) mighty or (figuratively) obstinate; make firm, harden, be(-come) strong.
(Aramaic) perhaps from {{h8199}}; judicial, i.e. a lawyer; sheriff.
from {{h6960}}; (compare {{h6961}}); literally a cord (as an attachment); figuratively, expectancy; expectation(-ted), hope, live, thing that I long for.
the same as {{h8615}}; Tikvah, the name of two Israelites; Tikvah.
from {{h6965}}; resistfulness; power to stand.

a primitive root; to manipulate, i.e. seize; chiefly to capture, wield, specifically, to overlay; figuratively, to use unwarrantably; catch, handle, (lay, take) hold (on, over), stop, × surely, surprise, take.
from the base of {{h8608}}; a smiting, i.e. (figuratively) contempt; tabret.
the same as {{h8611}}; Topheth, a place near Jerusalem; Tophet, Topheth.
probably a form of {{h8612}}; Tophteh, a place of cremation; Tophet.
of foreign derivation; Tartak, a deity of the Avvites; Tartak.

a primitive root; to clatter, i.e. slap (the hands together), clang (an instrument); by analogy, to drive (a nail or tent-pin, a dart, etc.); by implication, to become bondsman by handclasping); blow (a trumpet), cast, clap, fasten, pitch (tent), smite, sound, strike, × suretiship, thrust.
a denominative from {{h7275}} in the sense of throwing over; to transfer, i.e. translate; interpret.
from {{h7290}}; a lethargy or (by implication) trance; deep sleep.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8623}}; mighty, strong.
from {{h7783}} in the original sense of stretching out after; a longing; desire.
ordinal from {{h8672}}; ninth; ninth.
from {{h7788}} in the sense of arrival; a gift; present.
from {{h8630}}; might or (figuratively) positiveness; authority, power, strength.
from {{h7660}}; checkered stuff (as reticulated); broidered.
of uncertain derivation; Tirchanah, an Israelite; Tirhanah.
of uncertain derivation; Terach, the father of Abraham; also a place in the Desert; Tarah, Terah.
probably from {{h7329}}; a species of tree (apparently from its slenderness), perhaps the cypress; cypress.
from {{h7322}} in the sense of its congener {{h7495}}; a remedy; medicine.

from {{h7321}}; clamor, i.e. acclamation of joy or a battle-cry; especially clangor of trumpets, as an alarum; alarm, blow(-ing) (of, the) (trumpets), joy, jubile, loud noise, rejoicing, shout(-ing), (high, joyful) sound(-ing).
formed as {{h8641}}; a sacrificial offering; oblation.
or תְּרֻמָה; (Deuteronomy 12:11), from {{h7311}}; a present (as offered up), especially in sacrifice or as tribute; gift, heave offering (shoulder), oblation, offered(-ing).
of foreign derivation; Tirhakah, a king of Kush; Tirhakah.
patrial from an unused name meaning recourse; a Tishbite or inhabitant of Tishbeh (in Gilead); Tishbite.
and תַּרְמוּת; or תַּרְמִית; from {{h7411}}; fraud; deceit(-ful), privily.
(Aramaic) feminine תַּרְתֵּין; corresponding to {{h8147}}; two; second,   twelve, two.
